.TH simple_shell 1 "March 2024" "1.0" "Holberton Simple Shell Manual"

.SH NAME
simple_shell \- a custom UNIX command line interpreter

.SH SYNOPSIS
.B simple_shell
[\fBno arguments\fR]

.SH DESCRIPTION
The \fBsimple_shell\fR program is a command-line interpreter that reads user commands and executes them.

.PP
Features include:
- Displaying a prompt and waiting for input.
- Executing commands and handling paths.
- Supporting basic built-in commands like exit and env.

.SH USAGE
Interactive mode:
.RS
Launch the shell by running:
.br
\fB./hsh\fR
.br
Type a command followed by Enter.
.RE

.PP
Non-interactive mode:
.RS
Commands can be piped into the shell, e.g.:
.br
\fBecho \"ls -l\" | ./hsh\fR
.RE

.SH BUILT-IN COMMANDS
\fBexit\fR - Exit the shell.
.br
\fBenv\fR - Print the current environment variables.

.SH EXAMPLES
Interactive mode:
.RS
$ ./hsh
.br
$ ls -l
.br
$ exit
.RE

Non-interactive mode:
.RS
\fBecho \"ls -l\" | ./hsh\fR
.br
.RE

.SH AUTHOR
Luis Feliciano and Tommy Hernandez

.SH SEE ALSO
sh(1), bash(1), execve(2)

.SH BUGS
No known bugs at this time.

